verbose_text: Results of the X-ray scans of the gallium cut hooks (dual beam SEM) of H. holospinus show differential composition and distribution of metals in different hook parts, with the calcium and phosphorus being considerably higher at the basal arch of hooks where tension and strength are paramount compared to the hook tip and edge where the level of sulfur was considerably higher (XREF_TABLE, XREF_FIG and XREF_FIG).
